The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Overseas firms pick up 27% in Assam Co

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, May 11: The government has okayed an investment of Rs 188.32 crore by three Mauritius-based financial institutions ? Mavi Investment Fund, Lotus Global Investments and Invest India Limited ? in Assam Co Ltd.

 Assam Co has issued 2.7 crore warrants each of Re 1 face value on a private placement basis. A premium of Rs 22.25 has been charged on each warrant. The three FIs will hold 26.64 per cent in Assam Co.

 The investment will be made in Assam and Nagaland for cultivation, manufacture and sale of tea, said the Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB), which cleared the proposal. 

 The FIPB today cleared 26 proposals for foreign direct investment which will bring Rs 282.71 crore into the country. 

 The other big proposals cleared by finance minister P. Chidambaram on the recommendation of the FIPB include Itochu Corporation and UK-based Goldshield Groups Rs 44.54-crore proposal each.

 Itochu Corporation will set up a subsidiary to carry on trading of items sourced from the small-scale sector. The Japanese firm will have up to 100 per cent stake in the Indian subsidiary. Itochu has not disclosed the location of the proposed subsidiary.

 Goldshield Group plc will set up a holding company in Goa for making downstream investments in real estate development projects. 




